in nearly the same dps.<br><br>He argued that u should always want the best possible damage striking all the time, but of course in the situation it would be at the expense of a worse offhand ratio.<br><br><br>Anyways I eventually broke out the dps calc, found here on this board somewhere, and figured both combos at my current haste of 36%:<br><br>JM main/ SBoZ off = 1795 dpm<br>SBoZ main/ JM off = 1831 dpm<br><br>The SBoZ in prim would do essentially 36 more damage per minute than the JM in main<br><br>So he was correct.<br><br>However. <br><br>I still made the point of damage mitigation, in that with a lower average damage in your offhand u will be mitigated down to 1 more often.<br><br>Example:  average damage per hit for prim is let’s say 45 and offhand is 35. And average amount of damage mitigated by mobs ac is somewhere between 10-40, the offhand would be mitigated down to 1 more often than the primary.<br><br>Question is if this effect helps balance out the two combos or does it give an advantage to one or the either?<br><br>Overall though I personally still cling to the fastest wep in main, and best ratio in off, but situation like this I think are a bit more complicated than that.<br><br>What do u think? <br><br>Note: if I’m wrong about anything please feel free to call me out and pronounce me as a newb, but don’t forget to correct me =)<br> <p><p><table width="320" border="0"> <tr> <td> <div align="center"><p> <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1" color="#FFFFFF"><img name="pimp2" src="http://www.msu.edu/user/cooking3/dm/pimp2.jpg" width="192" height="250" border="0" usemap="#m_pimp2"><map name="m_pimp2"><area shape="rect" coords="49,99,139,142" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=120437" ></map><br><a >Touch the gold baby!</a></font face= "Arial,Helvectica,sansserif" size="-1" color="#FFFFFF"><br><a >Duridain 60 Pimp Daddy Warlord</a></font> <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1" colo